Hi Francois,

You are right, this is one way of doing this.

However, I prefer not to put this logic in a build file.

Usally, the ant build file I use just contains this:

...
&lt;batchtest fork=&quot;yes&quot;&gt;
	&lt;fileset dir=&quot;${classes.dir}&quot;&gt;
		&lt;include name=&quot;com/something/**/Test*.class&quot;/&gt;
	&lt;/fileset&gt;
&lt;/batchtest&gt;
...

If I start to put all kinds of exceptions at this single place, things will
get messy very quickly.

Regards,

tt

&gt; One thing you might want to try is to use Ant to run your unit tests. 
&gt; In Ant, you would use different batch tests to test the lower level 
&gt; parts, the the next higher part, etc. etc.
&gt; 
&gt; Hope that helps !
&gt; Francois
&gt; 
&gt; Taras Tielkes wrote:
&gt; &gt; Hi,
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; I have a layered API class model that I&#39;d like to unit test.
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; The API is layered in the sense that some high level APIs 
&gt; depend on lower
&gt; &gt; level APIs. Other higher level APIs are built on the high 
&gt; level APIs.
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; I have written unit tests for each of these APIs.
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; These unit tests can be run in any sequence, however: I&#39;d 
&gt; like to specify
&gt; &gt; that the unit tests for the lower level APIs should be run first.
&gt; &gt; When these tests pass, the higher level APIs can be tested, 
&gt; having some
&gt; &gt; confidence that the lower level works.
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; The reason is that when an error occurs in a low level API, 
&gt; it&#39;s easier to
&gt; &gt; diagnose when it occurs in the unit test for the lower 
&gt; level API, rather
&gt; &gt; than as a result of the higher level API calling the low level API.
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; When I add tests to a TestSuite using one of the addXXX() 
&gt; methods, is the
&gt; &gt; sequence of adding the tests the same sequence if which the 
&gt; tests are run?
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; If not, how can specify that a subset of all tests &#39;should&#39; 
&gt; be run in some
&gt; &gt; sequence? (Note: not *must*, the unit tests can still be 
&gt; run in *any*
&gt; &gt; sequence, but I&#39;d like the stuff that tests the low level 
&gt; parts of the code
&gt; &gt; to run first)
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; If TestSuite does not respect the sequence of the addXXX() 
&gt; calls for the
&gt; &gt; running of the tests, can I implements this by extending TestSuite?
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; Thanks in advance for any comments on this! (I&#39;m pretty new 
&gt; to unit testing
&gt; &gt; in general)
&gt; &gt; 
